      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISTER DEVEREAUX (4) finished second two starts back at Melton then was most impressive two-and-a-half weeks ago over 2150m at Bendigo, scoring by 18 metres after taking control of the race a long way from home. Meets some better types this time but another win is on the cards. RIDETHELIGHTNING (1) was out of the money two runs ago then broke and finished fourth last start over 2100m at Geelong, coming home 7 metres from the winner. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Needs to get it right to beat this field but he is up to the job. REVERAND BOB (5) must be considered after he finished runner-up over 1650m at Bendigo a week-and-a-half ago. SOLOTREKK (7) must be respected after scoring first-up last start by a nose at Bendigo over 1650m.",
